args:
A sweet Valentine's mood has settled over the
castle, and Orion—a man with oh-so-much love
to give—is looking for a date. He ends up
exasperated at the prince—who isn't quite so
into the idea—before taking him out on the town
under the pretext of learning to escort a lady.
Which of these ribbons do you like best?\nThe red one holds a certain charm,\nbut the blue is also quite nice...
Hmm... I'm rather at a loss.\nPerhaps we should think on it.
The treats are almost done, after all.\nLet's head back to the kitchen.
Grr! The nerve of that old man...\nI'll MAKE him acknowledge my charm!
Wowzers! Everyone's a busy bee today!
You think so as well, my faerie lady?
Yep! I guess it's because of Valentine's.
It most certainly seems that way.\nEveryone is toiling away to let those\nclose to them know just how they feel.
Love burns within each of their hearts...\nAh, but it is simply wonderful!
Uh oh. Hildegarde is on the\nrampage again.
This current atmosphere of flippant\nfrivolity in this castle makes an\nabsolute mockery of order!
I dunno if it's THAT bad...
It is like that because it is Valentine's!\n'Tis an event for sharing one's feelings\nwith someone special, after all.
If people merely worked to show their\ngratitude EVERY day, there would be\nno need for any of this foolishness.
This is all happening because you\nlack diligence!
Ah, but the feelings people are hoping to\nshare are not limited to those of gratitude.
They also share words of LOVE!
What say you to this, Hildegarde?\nPerhaps you might listen to my own\nwords of love and adoration?
Ha ha ha! Ah, but I am not a man\nwho is so easily disheartened.
Perhaps you might join me for some tea,\nmy dear faerie?
...Blast! The maidens of this castle have\nerected walls of iron around their hearts!

And while I sometimes yearn to feel the
sweet intoxication of a true soul mate,
even brushing against the mere FRINGES
of love would satisfy me now.
...That's it! I need to go on a DATE!\nEven going out for a mere friendly\nexcursion would be enough for me.
How long have you been listening to me?

Still, you must understand my feelings,
no? Surely even YOU sometimes wish
for a date or two—or perhaps a dozen,
if you're feeling truly greedy.
...Hmm? You have no such desire? LIES!
...Ah, I see. So that's how it is.
You lack the confidence to squire the\nobject of your affections about town!
Luckily, I can assist you in this.\nLeave everything to me!

Ha ha ha! I can see by the puzzled
expression on your face that you have
NO idea what I am going on about.
Worry not—all will be explained soon.
I'm going to get some things ready,\nso if you would give me a little time?
Well, if one is to go on a date, one must\nhave their personal appearance in order.
And ON this date, I shall instruct you in\nthe fine art of escorting a loving partner.
We shall go on this date, you and I,\nthat you might drink deep from my\nwell of knowledge.
This is all about you—and certainly NOT\nbecause everyone else turned me down\nand I have far too much time on my hands.
Now then, shall we be off to our\nafternoon of delights and wonder?
